# Playground

Wzorce referencyjne: `definitions/nui-button.ts`, `definitions/nui-icon.ts`.

## Checklist

1. `src/playground/definitions/nui-{name}.ts`:
   - `NUI_{NAME}_DEFAULTS` — wartości początkowe panelu
   - `CONTROLS` — sekcje: Content, Appearance, Modifiers, State, Layout, HTML
   - `ATTRIBUTE_NAMES` — camelCase → kebab-case (`nuiType: 'nui-type'`)
   - `renderPreview` — live preview
   - export `nui{Name}Playground: PlaygroundDefinition`

2. Wpis w `playgroundRegistry` (`registry.ts`)

## renderPreview

Importuj z `../types.js`: `whenString`, `whenBoolean`, `whenStringNotDefault`.

```typescript
function renderPreview(props: PlaygroundProps): TemplateResult {
  return html`
    <nui-icon
      icon=${String(props.icon)}
      width=${whenStringNotDefault(props.width, '1em')}
      nui-type=${whenString(props.nuiType)}
      ?disabled=${whenBoolean(props.disabled)}
    ></nui-icon>
  `;
}
```

- Wymagane pola (np. `icon`): `String(props.icon)`
- Opcjonalne / puste: `whenString`
- Domyślne komponentu: `whenStringNotDefault(value, '1em')`
- W szablonie używaj nazw HTML (`icon-pos=`), nie camelCase

